28/11/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Pope Benedict XVI on Tuesday (November 28th) began a three-day visit to Turkey, the first paid by the pontiff to a mainly Muslim country. He said he would seek to promote dialogue and bridge differences. Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan held an airport meeting with the pope before flying to Riga for the NATO summit. A massive security operation is in effect for the papal visit, involving 15,000 police personnel. (Aksam, Milliyet, Vatan, AP, BBC - 28/11/06) 
